The paper deals with a natural language processing task of answering questions about an environment, which involves interpreting both the question and the environment using background knowledge. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses probabilistic programming to model environmental uncertainty, which could also make it relevant to Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
